The Presidency has said an online medium given particularly to fake news has published that Zahra, daughter of President Muhammadu Buhari, has fraudulently secured a job with the Petroleum Products Pricing Regulatory Agency (PPPRA). While Zahra, according to a statement by the special adviser media to the president, Femi Adesina just like any other Nigerian, can work wherever she secures employment, he hastened to add that the story is false in every material particular. “The publication is untrue, malicious, and meant to cast aspersions at the First Family, since the tendentious platform claims the job was secured fraudulently. ”All people of goodwill are enjoined to ignore the hack piece, masquerading as a news story,” he added .